@startuml
object Teacher
object "Student API" as StudentAPI
object "Student message delivery" as StudentMessageDelivery
object "Student message recipients" as StudentMessageRecipients
object "Discord recipient lookup" as DiscordRecipientLookup
object "Discord messaging" as DiscordMessaging
object "Class Discord API" as ClassDiscordAPI
object "Class channel post" as ClassChannelPost
object RecipientData <<database>>
Teacher --> StudentAPI : 1: send DM request
StudentAPI --> StudentMessageDelivery : 2: execute
StudentMessageDelivery --> StudentMessageRecipients : 3: load recipients
StudentMessageRecipients --> RecipientData : 4: SELECT students/classes
StudentMessageDelivery --> RecipientData : 5: load identities and class guilds
StudentMessageDelivery --> DiscordRecipientLookup : 6: resolve guild member
StudentMessageDelivery --> DiscordMessaging : 7: send direct message
StudentMessageDelivery --> StudentAPI : 8: delivery results
Teacher --> ClassDiscordAPI : 9: channel post request
ClassDiscordAPI --> ClassChannelPost : 10: execute
ClassChannelPost --> RecipientData : 11: load class Discord binding
ClassChannelPost --> DiscordMessaging : 12: send channel message
@enduml
